# D{{N}} — ADR Dependency Graph

**Audience:** Architect + new joiners (decision archaeology).
**When to look at this:** When onboarding to a project, when proposing a new ADR ("does this conflict with anything?"), when auditing decision lineage. Especially valuable past 10+ ADRs where prose-walks become impractical.
**Prose gap closed:** ADRs cite each other in prose; this diagram shows the **decision lineage** as a DAG so superseded chains and conflict-with pairs are visible at a glance.

